# FinPuls environment template
#
# Local development
# 1) Copy this file to .env.local
# 2) Fill one or more provider keys below
# 3) Restart `npm run dev` after changes
#
# Production (Vercel)
# 1) Project Settings -> Environment Variables
# 2) Add NEWSAPI_KEY, GNEWS_API_KEY, ALPHAVANTAGE_API_KEY, NEXT_PUBLIC_FMP_API_KEY
# 3) Redeploy after updating variables
#
# Production (AWS example)
# - Store keys in AWS Secrets Manager (or Parameter Store)
# - Inject values into process env at runtime during deploy/start
#
# Provider chain order: NewsAPI -> GNews -> Alpha Vantage -> Financial Modeling Prep
# Add at least one key to get live data; otherwise fallback demo stories are used.

# 1) NewsAPI (https://newsapi.org)
# Free plan note: top-headlines and rate limits apply by account tier.
NEWSAPI_KEY=

# 2) GNews (https://gnews.io)
# Free plan note: daily request quotas apply.
GNEWS_API_KEY=

# 3) Alpha Vantage (https://www.alphavantage.co)
# Free plan note: per-minute and daily limits apply.
ALPHAVANTAGE_API_KEY=

# 4) Financial Modeling Prep (https://financialmodelingprep.com)
# Used by the server route as an additional fallback provider.
NEXT_PUBLIC_FMP_API_KEY=
